5: Mr. Bunny, Ms. Kitty, Mr. Puppy too!
9:
They're all my bestest, bestest
friends.
14:
You've sure been in a good mood
after meeting up with your Little
Lyrical friends.
18:
Yeah! I'm so happy I got to see
Kyoka and Misogi again!
20:
Nothing makes me happier than
when the three of us get to be
together!
23:
Everyone looks up to me in Little
Lyrical, after all!
31:
Well, Misogi's nine years old, and
Kyoka's only eight! I'm the oldest at
ten, so I'm like their big sister!
35:
Okay! As the Guild Master, I've gotta
do my best to find a way back home—
45:
Mimi, wait! It's dangerous to go
alone!
50:
I guess I'm not much of a Guild
Master, after all...
53:
I'm their big sister... So I've gotta do
better than this...
66:
You put others first whenever you
take action. That's a fine quality for a
leader to have, don't you think?
98:
That piggie... It seemed scared... And
somehow lonely, too!
101:
Well, I looked after that boar in the
past, and...
107:
I see. The boar was injured, so you
took it in as a pet until it escaped
one day...
110:
I'm glad it survived on its own. They
say it can be tough for an animal to
survive in the wild after living as a
pet.
111:
But it's been tearing up the fields
recently. So I thought maybe I could
tame it again, and then...
114:
Right... Well, I don't think your boar is
going to struggle out in the wild,
but...
118:
...D-don't worry, okay? You two got to
meet again, didn't you?
122:
It might take a while, but I'm sure
you can be friends again one day!
125:
Aww, thank you.
But... Unfortunately, it's over. The
village has already decided to hunt
down my old friend.
127:
...You saw me, I was doing my best
to calm it down just a minute ago.
Sadly, I think the time has come...
132: Does it REALLY have to end like this?
136: What do you want to do, Mimi?
140: I want to help out the piggie!
148:
W-wait! What do you mean? How're
you going to help?
152:
I don't think your friend forgot
anything! It just didn't recognize you
at first!
161:
Right... We can refresh the beast's
memory with the scent of these old
garments.
171: It will! I'm sure of it!
177:
No, stop! You know him! Try to
remember!
180:
You were lost and lonely this whole
time, weren't you...
184:
But it's okay now. This man
remembers you!
188: Do you... remember? It's me, buddy...
190:
I'm so sorry... I shouldn't have left you
all alone!
202:
Hehe... I was a little scared by the
piggie's size, but I'm okay now!
205:
Having a friend is the bestest thing
in the world.
223: I'd expect nothing less, Guild Master.
